tates, we set integral upper limits at 95\\% confidence\nlevel for energies above 200 GeV at $2.6\\times10^{-12}$~photons\ncm$^{-2}$s$^{-1}$ and $1.0\\times10^{-11}$~photons cm$^{-2}$s$^{-1}$,\nrespectively. We rule out steady VHE gamma-ray emission above this energy\nrange, at the level of the MAGIC sensitivity, originating in the interaction\nbetween the relativistic jet and the surrounding medium, while the emission\nabove this flux level produced inside the binary still remains a valid\npossibility.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 11 Aug 2017 20:03:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-30"}
