 accretion,\nthe other, exhibiting apparent transient variability without presence of an\naccretion disc. Our analysis confirms the existing census of substellar cluster\nmembers down to $\\approx$ 7 Mj. The zero result from our companion search\nagrees with the low occurrence rate of wide companions to brown dwarfs found in\nother works.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 11 Aug 2017 21:39:14 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 22 Aug 2017 02:18:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-12-13"}
